body:
The first ones by search. 

The last is almost by chance. The aggregator is made by one of the anons that follows Q. I came across Q by a lone link on reddit on the_donald that was deleted almost right after I clicked on it. Did some research, found my way to 8kun. What’s in the aggregator is posted on 8kun, it’s a just a simplifying tool that gets faster access, was dropped on the board at some point. 

So some luck, but also being in a place where other interesting people drop things. If you are looking for good information at some point you’ll getting closer to it. Information networks are changing all the time so it’s difficult because of increasing censorship. Like the donald on reddit doesn’t exist anymore. I came in during a sweet spot and learned from the users there. Now if you go to reddit such information is harder to find or no longer allowed there. But I was already a Trump supporter when I searched for trump stuff on reddit. Today if I was a Trump supporter coming to the Internet, I’d search google or YouTube and probably find TD.win, Ruqqus, parlor, gab, twitter, maybe discord, so I find one branch and find where I liked getting info from or search for purest source of information. Nowadays it might be a diaspora rather than a magnet. But it really depends on how aggressive you are in forming that info network, guest hosted on a show > find their channel. Link in the comments to a more gated community > check it out. Meme with a watermark by the maker > search for where that maker is originally posting from. Lone mysterious comment trying to evade the censorship algorithm > check it out. 

TD.win also crowdsources info. There are different information network. Ruqqus is an outpost, a frontier. So you won’t see as much of happening here as other established hubs of info with lots of users. On the donald for example maybe just one personal really like the Epoch Times so they always post those immediately and another user follows FOIA drops so they always post those and another users follows the ICE twitter account and posts those and another account follows the congressman in his state and posts their goings on. Now I’m observant and curious, so I have learned to pull all of those sources myself and regularly check them. But most users aren’t like that. In a big forum you are just passively intaking the flow from many many users.  

I don’t know how Luk gets his info, it’s different from what I have in my networks, although I don’t check mainstream news. But I like that because I benefit from seeing that. What I like about Ruqqus growing is that there are more users pulling from their own information networks, so I learn and I also don’t have to worry about catching as much, because other users bring it here. Trying to cover all bases is a lot.
